<TITLE> Proposed duty threatens homegrown industries: IBFB </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 14 (bdnews24.com)  The International Business Forum of Bangladesh (IBFB) Thursday expressed concern over the proposed increase in import duties on industrial raw materials and capital machinery in the budget for 2007-08. In its reaction to the budget, the forum said the proposed duty structure would threaten local industries and encourage imports. "Local textile products would face risk losing competitiveness in the global market," IBFB said in a statement Thursday. The forum however praised the government for the big allocation to agriculture research and diesel subsidy as well. The IBFB said additional allocations and policy supports were needed for the social and services sectors to attain the projected 7 percent GDP growth. It also demanded that import duties on hospital and medical equipment be reduced to help the health services improve and check the flow of well-off people seeking healthcare abroad. Proposed duty on computer and accessories would have a negative impact on ICT growth, it said. bd
